{{Quote|I was not permitted to enter the chamber where the Jedi High Council sat. It was described as a circular room in one of the four towers where the Masters of the day met to discuss the affairs of the Jedi.|An explorer, possibly [[Gammit Chond]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Alien Archive">''[[Star Wars: Alien Archive]]''</ref>}}
The '''Jedi Council Chamber''', also known as '''Jedi High Council Chamber''', was the meeting place of the [[Jedi High Council]]. It was located in the [[High Council Tower]]&mdash;one of the four [[Council Towers]]&mdash;of the [[Imperial Palace|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant]].<ref name="CL 2016">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> After the [[Proclamation of the New Order|rise]] of the [[Galactic Empire]], the Temple was transformed into the Imperial Palace of [[Galactic Emperor|Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Palpatine]]. Shortly afterward, the Emperor turned the Council Chamber into his private office.<ref name="Tarkin" />

==Description==
The [[Jedi High Council|Jedi Council]] Chamber contained twelve chairs, with each customized to suit the needs of the [[Jedi Master|Masters]]. These chairs formed a ring around a fern-patterned floor.<ref name="Everything">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know]]''</ref> This circular arrangement of the seats helped foster a sense that all members of the council had equal importance. The room had large windows that allowed in natural [[Star|sunlight]], bathing the council in the light of [[the Force]].<ref name="VE">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref>

